cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as translation and part-of-speech tagging, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of autoencoders, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The exploration of the structure of the representation space and the clustering of sentences based on syntactic similarity suggest a focus on neural networks and optimization, which are relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Lastly, the paper mentions the generation of pseudo-English sentences, which could involve computer vision techniques for image captioning, falling under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
